{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17646546","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17646546"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:32:17+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:32:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18190"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18190","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18190"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.23,0.53,0.08,0.05,0.13]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10904"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79340"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10904","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10904"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18190"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64662"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25352"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25355"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79340","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79340"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe intervertebral disc consists of two main components: the central nucleus pulposus and the surrounding annulus fibrosus.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary function of the annulus fibrosus?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Absorbs compressive forces during movement","Contains the nucleus pulposus and provides structural support","Enables rotation between vertebrae","Maintains disc hydration","Supplies nutrients to the disc"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Econtains the nucleus pulposus and provides structural support\u003C/strong\u003E is the primary function of the annulus fibrosus. It consists of concentric rings of tough collagen fibres that form a strong outer wall around the nucleus pulposus, maintaining disc integrity during movement.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAbsorbs compressive forces during movement\u003C/strong\u003E - This is primarily the role of the nucleus pulposus\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEnables rotation between vertebrae\u003C/strong\u003E - While the annulus fibrosus allows for spinal movement, this is not its primary function\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMaintains disc hydration\u003C/strong\u003E - Disc hydration is maintained through osmotic pressure within the nucleus pulposus\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESupplies nutrients to the disc\u003C/strong\u003E - Nutrients reach the disc through diffusion via the vertebral endplates\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe annulus fibrosus works together with the nucleus pulposus to allow controlled movement while maintaining disc stability. Its organised fibre arrangement provides resistance to various mechanical forces.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The annulus fibrosus is a tough, fibrous ring that surrounds and contains the nucleus pulposus in intervertebral discs.","The primary function of the annulus fibrosus is to maintain structural integrity of the intervertebral disc.","The annulus fibrosus consists of concentric layers of collagen fibres arranged in alternating orientations."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Henson B, Kadiyala B, Edens MA. Anatomy, Back, Muscles. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537074/","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Rockwood, C. A., Wirth, M. A., \u0026 Fehringer, E. V. (2016). Rockwood and Matsen\u0027s The Shoulder E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","DeSai C, Reddy V, Agarwal A. Anatomy, Back, Vertebral Column. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK525969/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64662"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18190"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64662","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64662"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-14T10:11:56+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-14T10:13:26+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10904"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79340"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},